---
id: dxos.plugin.chess
name: ChessPlugin
version: 0.2.0
extends: [dxos.plugin.chess@0.1.0]
---

Extends chess-1 to introduce UI components: the game Lobby and the Gameboard.

## Extensions

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | dxos.org/ext/type@1.0          |
| `feat`      | dxos.org/ext/feat@1.0          |
| `test`      | dxos.org/ext/test@1.0          |
| `component` | dxos.org/ext/component@1.0     |

## Types

New types introduced in this version.

```type Player
  fields:
    id: string
    name: string
    color: Color
```

```type GameStatus
  variants: waiting | active | finished
```

```type Game
  fields:
    id: string
    players: Player[2]
    board: Board
    status: GameStatus
    winner?: Player
```

## Components

```component Lobby
  desc: Entry point where players create or join a game.
  props:
    playerId: string
  state:
    games: Game[]               # list of open/active games
    selected?: Game
  slots:
    header?: ReactNode
    empty?: ReactNode           # shown when games list is empty
  actions:
    createGame() → Game
    joinGame(game: Game) → Game
    spectate(game: Game)
  emits:
    onJoin(game: Game)
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [header slot]           │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │ Game list               │
    │  ┌───────────────────┐  │
    │  │ game row          │  │
    │  └───────────────────┘  │
    │  [empty slot]           │
    ├─────────────────────────┤
    │ [Create Game]           │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

```component Gameboard
  desc: Interactive chess board for an active game.
  props:
    game: Game
    playerId: string            # identifies which side the viewer plays
  state:
    selected?: Square           # currently selected square
    highlights: Square[]        # legal move targets for selected piece
    perspective: Color          # which side is at the bottom (default: player's color)
  slots:
    toolbar?: ReactNode
    sidebar?: ReactNode
    overlay?: ReactNode         # e.g. checkmate / promotion dialogs
  actions:
    selectSquare(square: Square)
    submitMove(move: Move)
    flipBoard()
  emits:
    onMove(move: Move)
    onResign()
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────┐
    │ [toolbar slot]          │
    ├──────────┬──────────────┤
    │          │ [sidebar]    │
    │  8×8     │              │
    │  board   │ move history │
    │          │              │
    ├──────────┴──────────────┤
    │ [overlay slot]          │
    └─────────────────────────┘
```

## Features

```feat F-3: Lobby

  req F-3.1: Player sees list of open games on entering the Lobby.
  req F-3.2:
    when: player creates a game
    then: new Game created with status waiting; player assigned white

  req F-3.3:
    when: second player joins an open game
    then: Game.status transitions to active; joining player assigned black

  req F-3.4:
    when: Game.status becomes active
    then: both players navigated to Gameboard
```

```feat F-4: Gameboard

  req F-4.1:
    when: player selects a square containing their piece
    then: legal move targets highlighted on board

  req F-4.2:
    when: player selects a highlighted target square
    then: Move submitted via submitMove(); board updated on success

  req F-4.3:
    when: pawn reaches the back rank
    then: promotion dialog shown via overlay slot; player selects piece kind

  req F-4.4:
    when: Game.status is finished
    then: result overlay shown (winner or draw); further moves disabled
```

## Acceptance

```test T-3: Create and join game
  given: two players are in the Lobby
  when: player A creates a game, player B joins it
  then:
    - Game.status === active
    - Game.players[0].color === white   # creator
    - Game.players[1].color === black   # joiner
    - both players see the Gameboard
```

```test T-4: Legal move highlight
  given: Gameboard is shown, it is white's turn
  when: white selects the e2 pawn
  then:
    - squares e3 and e4 are highlighted
    - no other squares are highlighted
```

```test T-5: Pawn promotion
  given: white pawn is on e7, it is white's turn
  when: white moves pawn to e8
  then:
    - promotion overlay appears
    - after player selects queen, Move recorded with promotion: queen
    - board shows white queen on e8
```

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Definitions for extensions introduced in this version.
Extensions inherited from chess-1 (type, feat, test) are not repeated.

```ext component
  uri: dxos.org/ext/component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap            # external inputs (immutable inside component)
    state?: FieldMap            # internal reactive state
    slots?: FieldMap            # named ReactNode injection points
    actions?: ActionMap         # methods the component exposes or handles
    emits?: EventMap            # events the component raises to its parent
    layout?: CodeBlock          # ASCII sketch of visual structure (non-normative)
```
